org.shininet.bukkit.playerheads

Class Lang

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.shininet.bukkit.playerheads.Lang

  • public final class Lang
extends Object
    Defines localization support for the plugin in way of messages and item names. The values of keys defined here can be changed in lang.properties. `HEAD_SPAWN_*` entries are strings used for spawning heads with the spawn command, `HEAD_*` entries are used to determine the display-name for a given head. Note: This documentation was inferred after the fact and may be inaccurate.
    Author:
    meiskam

    • Method Detail

      • getString

        public static String getString(String key)
        Gets the string value associated with a given language-file (localization) key. Note: localization strings will first be loaded from the plugin config path, and then from the default (internal) lang resource if the key is missing.
        Parameters:
        key - the key to get the message string for
        Returns:
        the localized message string for the key

      • init

        public static void init(org.bukkit.plugin.Plugin instance)
        Associates the class with a plugin and reloads all localized strings.
        Parameters:
        instance - the plugin instance being used.

      • reload

        public static void reload()
        Reloads localization resources and reloads the values of all keys. Note: localization strings will first be loaded from the plugin config path, and then from the default lang resource if missing.
        See Also:
        reload()
